### Get all users
GET http://localhost:5168/api/users

### Get user by ID
GET http://localhost:5168/api/users/1

### Get user that doesn't exist
GET http://localhost:5168/api/users/99

### Create a new user
POST http://localhost:5168/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "issam",
    "lastName": "Wonder",
    "email": "alice@example.com",
    "username": "alicewonder",
    "role": "User"
}

### Update a user
PUT http://localhost:5168/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "John Updated",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "john.updated@example.com",
    "username": "johndoe",
    "role": "Admin",
    "isActive": true
}

### Delete a user
DELETE http://localhost:5168/api/users/5
```

---

## 👀 How to Send Requests

In VS Code, open `requests.http` — you'll see **"Send Request"** appearing above each request like this:
```
### Get all users        ← click "Send Request" above this
GET http://localhost:5168/api/users


### Login
POST http://localhost:5168/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "johndoe",
    "password": "Admin123"
}

### Try without token (should fail)
GET http://localhost:5168/api/users

### Try with token (should work)
GET http://localhost:5168/api/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..kX49_GcU1pFx-rGpDRvKQ5Q6q3nMJUGnmswzgtGTcxk

### Get all AD users (need token!)
GET http://localhost:5168/api/ad/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..rNA65KsN8n1Ks_nAN43j-9k4EmFrVWa78ipilkR3dPA

### Test AD route
GET http://localhost:5168/api/ad/users
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..rNA65KsN8n1Ks_nAN43j-9k4EmFrVWa78ipilkR3dPA